Report all configured GDAL drivers for raster formats

Source: R/RcppExports.R
gdal_formats.Rd

gdal_formats() prints to the console a list of the supported raster formats.

Usage

gdal_formats()

Value

No return value, called for reporting only.

Examples

gdal_formats()
#> Supported raster formats:
#>   VRT (rw+): Virtual Raster
#>   DERIVED (ro): Derived datasets using VRT pixel functions
#>   GTiff (rw+): GeoTIFF
#>   COG (w): Cloud optimized GeoTIFF generator
#>   NITF (rw+): National Imagery Transmission Format
#>   RPFTOC (ro): Raster Product Format TOC format
#>   ECRGTOC (ro): ECRG TOC format

#>   SAR_CEOS (ro): CEOS SAR Image
#>   CEOS (ro): CEOS Image
#>   JAXAPALSAR (ro): JAXA PALSAR Product Reader (Level 1.1/1.5)
#>   GFF (ro): Ground-based SAR Applications Testbed File Format (.gff)
#>   ELAS (rw+): ELAS
#>   ESRIC (ro): Esri Compact Cache
#>   AIG (ro): Arc/Info Binary Grid
#>   AAIGrid (rw): Arc/Info ASCII Grid
#>   GRASSASCIIGrid (ro): GRASS ASCII Grid
#>   ISG (ro): International Service for the Geoid
#>   SDTS (ro): SDTS Raster
#>   DTED (rw): DTED Elevation Raster
#>   PNG (rw): Portable Network Graphics
#>   JPEG (rw): JPEG JFIF
#>   MEM (rw+): In Memory Raster

#>   BIGGIF (ro): Graphics Interchange Format (.gif)
